# Alembic Database Migrations

Cutover Date: 2026-07-12

From this date forward, all database schema changes must be managed via Alembic. Manual SQL migration scripts (e.g. `migrate_v*.py`) are deprecated and must not be added.

## Working with Migrations

### For Existing Databases (Stamping)
If you are deploying this code to an environment with an existing database that has already run the legacy migrations up to v6:
```bash
python -m alembic stamp head
```
This marks the database as up-to-date with the baseline migration revision (`93ffbe56c9bc`) without re-running any schema changes.

### For New Databases / Fresh Installation
1. Initialize the tables using the metadata script:
   ```bash
   python init_db_tables.py
   ```
2. Stamp the database to register the initial baseline revision:
   ```bash
   python -m alembic stamp head
   ```

### Creating New Migrations
When you modify models in `app/models.py`, generate a new migration script using:
```bash
python -m alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe your changes"
```
Review the generated file in `alembic/versions/` and then run:
```bash
python -m alembic upgrade head
```